### Authorization Tests
### Test Role-based Access Control (RBAC)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

# ==========================================
# STEP 1: Login and Get Tokens
# ==========================================

### Register Admin User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin-test@example.com",
  "password": "Admin@123456",
  "fullName": "Admin User"
}

### Register Customer User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "customer-test@example.com",
  "password": "Customer@123456",
  "fullName": "Customer User"
}

### Login as Admin
# @name loginAdmin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin-test@example.com",
  "password": "Admin@123456"
}

### Login as Customer
# @name loginCustomer
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "customer-test@example.com",
  "password": "Customer@123456"
}

### Save Admin Token
@adminToken = {{loginAdmin.response.body.accessToken}}

### Save Customer Token
@customerToken = {{loginCustomer.response.body.accessToken}}

# ==========================================
# STEP 2: Test Admin-Only Endpoints
# ==========================================

### ✅ Test 1: Admin can access GET /users (ADMIN only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### ❌ Test 2: Customer cannot access GET /users (should return 403)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

###

### ❌ Test 3: No token for GET /users (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&pageSize=10

###

### ✅ Test 4: Admin can access GET /users/email/:email (ADMIN only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/email/customer-test@example.com
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### ❌ Test 5: Customer cannot access GET /users/email/:email (should return 403)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/email/customer-test@example.com
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

###

### ✅ Test 6: Admin can deactivate user (ADMIN only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/user-123/deactivate
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### ❌ Test 7: Customer cannot deactivate user (should return 403)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/user-123/deactivate
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

# ==========================================
# STEP 3: Test Endpoints that Allow Both Roles
# ==========================================

### ✅ Test 8: Admin can access GET /users/:id
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/user-123
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### ✅ Test 9: Customer can access GET /users/:id
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/user-123
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

###

### ✅ Test 10: Admin can update user
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/user-123
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Updated User",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

###

### ✅ Test 11: Customer can update user
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/user-123
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "My Updated Name",
  "phone": "0987654321"
}

# ==========================================
# STEP 4: Test Authentication Failures
# ==========================================

### ❌ Test 12: Missing Authorization header (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users

###

### ❌ Test 13: Invalid token format (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer invalid.token.here

###

### ❌ Test 14: Malformed Authorization header (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: InvalidFormat token

###

### ❌ Test 15: Empty Authorization header (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer

# ==========================================
# STEP 5: Test Authorization Error Messages
# ==========================================

### ❌ Test 16: Detailed 403 error message
# Expected response:
# {
#   "statusCode": 403,
#   "message": "Access denied. Required roles: ADMIN. Your role: CUSTOMER",
#   "error": "Forbidden"
# }
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

###

### ❌ Test 17: Multiple roles in error message
# If endpoint required both ADMIN and CUSTOMER but user has neither
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

# ==========================================
# STEP 6: Test Token Verification
# ==========================================

### ✅ Test 18: Verify valid token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{adminToken}}"
}

###

### ✅ Test 19: Get current user with valid token
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### ✅ Test 20: Get current user as customer
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

# ==========================================
# STEP 7: Test Edge Cases
# ==========================================

### ❌ Test 21: Token with missing role field (should return 401)
# This would require a malformed token - handled by AuthGuard

### ❌ Test 22: Token with invalid role (should return 401)
# This would be rejected during JWT verification

